Package com.cafean.CalcServer

Class JobQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.CalcServer.util.AbstractLoggable
      • com.cafean.CalcServer.JobQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    public class JobQueue
extends AbstractLoggable
implements java.lang.Runnable
    A class to provide a job queue to hold information concerning calculations submitted on this machine.

      • run

        public void run()
        The entry point for this thread. Checks the queue every TICK_LENGTH to determine whether to start a new calculation.
        Specified by:

      • beginServerIdleCount

        public void beginServerIdleCount()
        Indicates that a server idle count should be started. This count can be cancelled by calling cancelIdleCount(). Note that this count will not proceed while any calculations are currently running or waiting.

      • cancelServerIdleCount

        public void cancelServerIdleCount()
        Indicates that a server idle count should be canceled. This count can be restarted by calling beginIdleCount().

      • loadJob

        public int loadJob​(java.lang.String folderPath)
        Attempts to load the job at the given location by reading its CJF.
        Parameters:
        folderPath - the path to the local folder to load.
        Returns:
        > 0: the DBID of the job if successful or the job was already loaded.
        < 0: Error;
        -1 Folder not found.
        -2 CJF not found.
        -3 Failed to load job ( plug-in not available)
        -4 Failed to load job ( check log )
        -5 Failed to load job ( CJF format error )

      • findFolderContents

        public int findFolderContents​(FolderContentsRequest request)
        Retrieves a set of Job and Folder objects describing the contents of the requested folder

        Note that any or all of the returned Jobs may have in-memory loaded SnapRun objects. In this case, the DBID of the Job will be greater than zero.

        Parameters:
        request - the FolderContentsRequest to fill a response to
        Returns:
        0 for success or negative on error
        -1 Folder not found
        -2 Path not a folder -3 Cannot read folder (permission denied)

      • findCJFs

        public CalcJobFile[] findCJFs​(java.lang.String folderPath)
        Retrieves a set of CalcJobFile handles describing the contents of the given folder path.

        Note that any or all of the returned CalcJobFiles may have in-memory loaded SnapRun objects. In this case, the returned CJF is the backing for that SnapRun.

        Parameters:
        folderPath - a String containing the folder path to the folder for which to retrieve the job list. This folder should be in the form: /root/[folder/]

        public CalcJobFile findJobByFolderPath​(java.lang.String folderPath)
                                throws java.io.IOException
        Attempts to load the CJF for the job at the given location.
        Returns:
        the CalcJobFile requested. This method does not return null.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the CJF is not found or is not in CJF format.
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the URL format is unsupported.

      • unmountRootFolder

        public int unmountRootFolder​(RootFolder root)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        0 for success, -1 incomplete jobs found,

      • releaseJob

        public int releaseJob​(CalcJobFile calcJobFile)
        Attempts to release the given job by disposing of it's SnapRun and deleting the corresponding CJF file. Note: A jobRemoved notification is sent only for jobs managed by a SnapRun object. Clients that work with jobs that are not loaded must re-query the folder contents to update their display.
        Parameters:
        calcJobFile - the CalcJobFile representing the job to delete.
        Returns:
        0 = success

      • deleteJob

        public void deleteJob​(CalcJobFile calcJobFile,
                      boolean preserveInput,
                      boolean removeDependents)
               throws DeleteFailedException
        Attempts to delete the given job and it's related files.

        Note: A jobRemoved notification is sent only for jobs managed by a JobHandle object. Clients that work with jobs that are not loaded must re-query the folder contents to update their display.

        Parameters:
        calcJobFile - the CalcJobFile representing the job to delete.
        preserveInput -
        removeDependents - If true and the job has any dependent jobs then they will also be deleted.
        Throws:
        DeleteFailedException
